article.headline: Tennessee Tech 87, SE Missouri 80
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher scored 22 points and Amadi McKenzie added 20, and Tennessee Tech came back from an 18-point first-half deficit to beat Southeast Missouri State 87-80 on Saturday night. The Golden Eagles (10-9, 5-6 Ohio Valley) trailed 46-34 at the break but took the lead for good, 64-63, on Frank Davis' layup with 7:19 to go. The Redhawks (7-13, 5-6) hit seven 3-pointers in the first half but were 8-for-32 from the field in the second, including 1-for-11 from 3-point range. Belton Rivers added 19 points for Tennessee Tech, which has won five of its last six. David Johnson led Southeast Missouri State with 23 points and 10 rebounds, and Michael Rembert added 16 points.
